reviews.review_text: –> In agreement with njpg, this is a great companion to the classic audience recording. It adds the bottom end that the original lacks which is really welcome as Lesh is on fire, absolutely CRUSHING the middle jam in Morning Dew and generally digging the monstrous sound. Only drawback here is the occasional flanging which makes everything go out of tune, it's really noticeable in slow passages – Ship of Fools is almost unlistenable.
